  "prompt": "How can I dress for a foam party?",
  "response": "Dressing for a foam party requires careful consideration since you'll be getting wet and potentially messy. Here are some tips to help you choose the appropriate attire:\n\n1. **Swimwear:** Opt for swimsuits or board shorts. Swimwear is designed to handle water well and dries quickly. A bikini or one-piece for women and swim trunks for men are ideal.\n   \n2. **Light, Breathable Clothes:** If you prefer not to wear swimwear, choose lightweight and quick-drying clothes. Avoid heavy fabrics like denim; instead, go for items made of nylon or polyester.\n\n3. **Footwear:** Waterproof footwear such as flip flops or water shoes are best. Regular shoes or sneakers can get soaked and become uncomfortable, not to mention potentially ruined.\n\n4. **Protective Eyewear:** Foam can irritate your eyes, so consider wearing goggles if you feel you need extra protection.\n\n5. **Avoid Expensive Items:** Foam parties can be rough on clothes and accessories, so leave expensive jewelry, designer clothes, and anything you'd be upset to see ruined at home.\n\n6. **Cover-ups:** If you want an additional layer, wear a cover-up like a sarong, a casual dress, or a tank top which is easy to remove and put back on.\n\n7. **Secure Clothing:** Wear tightly secured clothing that won't shift or become problematic once wet, ensuring you remain comfortable and can move freely.\n\nRemember to bring a towel and a change of clothes for after the party, as you\u2019ll likely want to get out of wet apparel and into something dry.",
